INSERT INTO protocols (title, anatomicalSite, technique, modality, prescriptionDose, fractionation, targetVolume, oarConstraints, planningObjectives, beamArrangement, imagingRequirements, specialConsiderations, category, difficulty, estimatedPlanningTime, createdBy, isPublic, createdAt, updatedAt) VALUES
('Head and Neck IMRT - Definitive Treatment', 'Head and Neck', 'IMRT', 'Photon', '70 Gy', '35 fractions (2 Gy/fx)', 'PTV70 (primary tumor + involved nodes), PTV63 (high-risk subclinical), PTV56 (low-risk subclinical)', 'Spinal cord max <45 Gy, Brainstem max <54 Gy, Parotids mean <26 Gy (at least one <20 Gy), Mandible max <70 Gy, Larynx mean <45 Gy, Brachial plexus max <66 Gy', 'PTV70: V95% >95%, V107% <5%; PTV63: V95% >95%; PTV56: V95% >95%; Minimize hot spots >110%', '7-9 coplanar beams, avoid direct anterior/posterior beams through oral cavity, optimize beam angles to spare parotids and spinal cord', 'Planning CT with IV contrast, immobilization mask, PET-CT fusion for GTV delineation, daily CBCT for setup verification', 'SIB technique for simultaneous treatment of multiple PTVs, consider adaptive replanning at fraction 15-20 due to anatomic changes', 'imrt', 'advanced', 180, 1, 1, NOW(), NOW()),

('Prostate IMRT with Pelvic Nodes', 'Prostate', 'IMRT', 'Photon', '79.2 Gy / 50.4 Gy', '44 fractions (1.8 Gy/fx prostate, 1.8 Gy/fx nodes for 28 fx)', 'PTV prostate + seminal vesicles, PTV pelvic lymph nodes', 'Rectum V70 <20%, V60 <35%, V50 <50%; Bladder V70 <35%, V65 <50%; Femoral heads V50 <5%; Small bowel V45 <200cc', 'Prostate PTV: V95% >95%, V107% <2%; Nodal PTV: V95% >95% for 28 fractions then boost prostate only', '7-9 coplanar beams, avoid lateral beams through femoral heads, anterior oblique beams to spare rectum', 'Planning CT with full bladder and empty rectum protocol, fiducial markers for IGRT, daily CBCT or kV imaging', 'Sequential boost technique - treat nodes to 50.4 Gy then cone down to prostate; consider rectal spacer for dose reduction', 'imrt', 'intermediate', 120, 1, 1, NOW(), NOW()),

('Whole Breast IMRT with Boost', 'Breast', 'IMRT', 'Photon', '50 Gy / 60 Gy', '25 fractions (2 Gy/fx whole breast, 2 Gy/fx boost for 5 fx)', 'PTV whole breast, PTV tumor bed boost', 'Heart mean <4 Gy, V5 <40%; Ipsilateral lung V20 <20%, V5 <50%; Contralateral breast <3 Gy mean; Thyroid mean <20 Gy', 'Whole breast PTV: V95% >95%, dose homogeneity <107%; Boost PTV: V95% >95%', 'Tangential field-in-field or IMRT technique, 2-4 beams, optimize to minimize hot spots and improve homogeneity', 'Planning CT in treatment position with breast board, DIBH for left-sided cases to reduce heart dose, weekly port films or CBCT', 'Consider deep inspiration breath hold (DIBH) for left breast, sequential boost after whole breast treatment, assess for regional nodal irradiation', 'imrt', 'beginner', 90, 1, 1, NOW(), NOW()),

('Lung VMAT - SBRT Peripheral Tumor', 'Lung', 'VMAT', 'Photon', '54 Gy', '3 fractions (18 Gy/fx)', 'ITV (internal target volume from 4D-CT), PTV = ITV + 5mm', 'Total lung V20 <10%, mean lung dose <8 Gy; Spinal cord max <18 Gy; Esophagus max <27 Gy; Heart V30 <15cc; Chest wall V30 <30cc; Brachial plexus max <24 Gy', 'PTV: V100% >95%, conformity index 1.0-1.2, gradient index <5.0; Minimize dose to uninvolved lung', '2-3 partial or full arcs, non-coplanar beams if needed for superior tumors, avoid beams through contralateral lung', '4D-CT for motion assessment, ITV encompasses all respiratory phases, CBCT before each fraction, consider gating or tracking for motion >1cm', 'Peripheral tumor >2cm from proximal bronchial tree, heterogeneity correction mandatory, verify ITV adequacy with 4D-CBCT', 'vmat', 'advanced', 150, 1, 1, NOW(), NOW()),

('Esophageal Cancer VMAT', 'Esophagus', 'VMAT', 'Photon', '50.4 Gy', '28 fractions (1.8 Gy/fx)', 'PTV = GTV + involved nodes + 3-4cm superior/inferior + 1cm radial', 'Spinal cord max <45 Gy; Heart mean <26 Gy, V30 <46%, V40 <100cc; Lung V20 <30%, V5 <60%, mean <18 Gy; Liver mean <30 Gy', 'PTV: V95% >95%, V107% <2%; Minimize lung dose while maintaining target coverage', '2-3 arcs, avoid direct posterior beams through spinal cord, optimize to spare heart and lungs', 'Planning CT with IV contrast and oral contrast, PET-CT fusion for GTV delineation, 4D-CT if tumor near diaphragm, daily CBCT', 'Consider respiratory motion for lower third tumors, concurrent chemotherapy standard, elective nodal coverage per institutional guidelines', 'vmat', 'advanced', 135, 1, 1, NOW(), NOW()),

('Rectal Cancer VMAT with Boost', 'Rectum', 'VMAT', 'Photon', '50.4 Gy / 54 Gy', '28 fractions (1.8 Gy/fx, boost 1.8 Gy/fx for 2 fx)', 'PTV mesorectum and nodes, PTV tumor boost', 'Small bowel V45 <200cc, V40 <300cc; Bladder V50 <50%, mean <40 Gy; Femoral heads V40 <50%; Genitalia mean <20 Gy', 'Mesorectal PTV: V95% >95%; Boost PTV: V95% >95%; Minimize small bowel dose', '2 full arcs or 3-4 partial arcs, avoid direct anterior beams through bladder and small bowel', 'Planning CT with full bladder protocol, rectal contrast to delineate tumor, MRI fusion for improved GTV delineation, daily CBCT', 'Prone position with belly board to displace small bowel, full bladder to reduce small bowel in field, concurrent capecitabine', 'vmat', 'intermediate', 120, 1, 1, NOW(), NOW())
